    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it does feel like a dark moment, but that's the thing... i don't think the light can find its way back in. it's like the engine is dead. when the art was there, i felt alive, like i was part of something. now i'm just taking up space. i look in the mirror and i don't even recognize the person looking back. it's just a body moving through motions. does that even make sense? that you can just... cease to be, even while you're still breathing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
